parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can cause the seat belt to jam or become inoperable, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle is broken or crumbled
the red release button is broken
the seat belt is stuck or jammed
the seat belt will not unlatch or retract
the passenger is stuck in the seat belt.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed or Denied Seat Belt Recall Repairs
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay or denial of seat belt recall repairs can leave the vehicle in an unsafe condition, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The dealer does not have the parts
the dealer orders the wrong parts
the repair is delayed or denied
the vehicle is left in an unsafe condition.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inoperable rear lap belts can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of a crash, particularly for rear seat passengers.
symptoms: The rear lap belts are locked in place
the rear lap belts are inoperable
the rear lap belts will not pull out to fasten a passenger.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Ignition Switch Failure and Electrical Fires
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause electrical fires, which can lead to vehicle damage, injury, or even death. The proximity of the ignition switch to the air conditioning system and the fuel source (carburetor) increases the risk of a catastrophic fire.
symptoms: Ignition switch overheats
smoke emanates from the steering column
blower fan quits intermittently
short circuits in the ignition switch
and electrical fires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause electrical fires, which can lead to vehicle damage, injury, or even death. The lack of prior warning signs increases the risk of a sudden and unexpected fire.
symptoms: Wires rubbing against unpadded clamps
insulation worn off
electrical shorts
and fires starting under the carburetor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the horn can lead to a lack of audible warning in emergency situations, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Horn failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the engine without warning can cause loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly stops running without prior warning
unusual noises may be heard before the engine stalls
the vehicle may stall while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The overheating of the catalytic converter can cause a fire, potentially spreading to other parts of the vehicle, and posing a significant risk to the driver and occupants.
symptoms: The catalytic converter overheats
melting surrounding components such as firewalls and carpet
unusual noises or smells may be present
the vehicle may experience reduced performance or difficulty starting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the muffler can cause excessive noise, potentially leading to driver distraction, and may also be a sign of a more significant issue with the exhaust system.
symptoms: The muffler fails
causing excessive noise
the vehicle may experience reduced performance or difficulty starting
unusual vibrations or smells may be present.
